        "english": "Can you walk a little slower?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "gr_hsk2_003",
    "level": 2,
    "title": "Excessiveness with 太...了 (tài...le)",
    "pattern": "Subject + 太 + Adjective + 了",
    "explanation": "太...了 means 'too...' or 'so...!' The 了 at the end is mandatory and intensifies the adjective. It can be used positively ('so great!') or negatively ('too expensive!').",
    "examples": [
      {
        "simplified": "这个太贵了。",
        "traditional": "這個太貴了。",
        "pinyin": "Zhège tài guì le.",
        "english": "This is too expensive."
      },
      {
        "simplified": "太好了！",
        "traditional": "太好了！",
        "pinyin": "Tài hǎo le!",
        "english": "That's great!"
      }
    ],
    "fillBlanks": [
      {
        "sentence": "这个问题___难了。",
        "answer": "太",
        "distractors": ["很", "非常", "真"],
        "english": "This problem is too difficult."
      },
      {
        "sentence": "今天太热___！",
        "answer": "了",
        "distractors": ["吗", "呢", "吧"],
        "english": "Today is so hot!"
      },
      {
        "sentence": "那部电影___好看了。",
        "answer": "太",
        "distractors": ["很", "非常", "比较"],
        "english": "That movie is so good to watch."
      }
    ],
    "mcqSentences": [
      {
        "correct": "这件衣服太小了。",
        "wrong": ["这件衣服很太小。", "这件衣服太小。", "这件衣服小太了。"],
        "english": "This piece of clothing is too small."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
